	<!-- Post 3 -->
	<item>
		<title>Farm-to-Table: A Weekend Cooking Guide</title>
		<link>http://localhost/?p=22</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[liza]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There's something deeply satisfying about cooking with fresh, locally sourced ingredients. In this guide, we take you through a weekend of farm-to-table cooking that will delight your senses and nourish your soul.</p>

<h3>Saturday Morning: The Farmer's Market</h3>
<p>Start your weekend at the local farmer's market. Pick up seasonal vegetables, fresh herbs, artisan bread, and free-range eggs. Talk to the farmers — their passion and knowledge add an extra layer of appreciation to every meal.</p>

<h3>Saturday Evening: Rustic Dinner</h3>
<p>Prepare a simple yet elegant dinner: roasted root vegetables with rosemary, a fresh garden salad with homemade vinaigrette, and crusty bread with herb butter. Let the ingredients speak for themselves.</p>

<h3>Sunday Brunch</h3>
<p>Use the remaining eggs for a fluffy omelette filled with sautéed mushrooms and goat cheese. Pair it with fresh-squeezed orange juice and a strong cup of coffee.</p>

<p>Farm-to-table cooking isn't just about the food — it's about slowing down, connecting with your community, and savoring every bite.</p>]]></content:encoded>
